Dark Chocolate No Churn Ice Cream
  --Cook's Country

2 c heavy cream, chilled
1 c sweetened condensed milk
6 oz bittersweet chocolate, melted
1/4 c whole milk
1/2 c light corn syrup
2 tbsp sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/2 tsp instant espresso powder
1/4 tsp table salt

Process cream in blender until soft peaks form, 20-30 s. Scrape down sides of blender jar and continue to process until stiff peaks form, ~10 s longer. Using rubber spatula, stir in condensed milk, melted chocolate, whole milk, corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, espresso powder, and salt. Process until thoroughly combined, ~20 s, scraping down sides of blender jar as needed. Pour cream mixture into 8Â½ by 4 1/2" loaf pan. Press plastic wrap flush against surface of cream mixture. Freeze until firm, at least 6 hrs. Serve.


Notes: To melt the chocolate, microwave it in a bowl at 50 percent power for 2-3 min, stirring it occasionally. Makes ~1 qt
